AGI - It is likely that Pope Francis can be resigned. At least according to Cardinal Gianfranco Ravasi interviewed in the course of Non Stop News on Rtl. "I think he can do it, because he is a person who, from this point of view, is strong enough in his choices," he said. "He has long thought to continue his activity, even when, for example, there was the difficulty of the knee, which has changed the normal style of relation of the public figure with the entire world ecclesiastical community."
"On that occasion - Ravasi has remembered -, he had that famous joke according to which he governs with the brain and not with the knee. Therefore, there has always been a tendency to fight and react >, and it is also a legitimate choice, because it could even face trips in absolutely difficult and challenging conditions, such as that in the Far East. However, it is out of doubt that, if he was in a situation where his chance of having direct contacts was compromised - as he loves to do - to be able to communicate immediately, incisive and decisive, then I think he might decide to resign".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The Pope explicitly stated that he delivered the letter in the hands of the Secretary of State of the time, so it is a formal act," Ravasi continued, referring to the letter of resignation signed by Pope Francis in 2013 in the event of serious physical impediment. "I must say, instead - he added -, that I could see live the decision of Benedict XVI, because he had trusted me. In this case, he stated clearly that yes, there was still the possibility, at least from the head up, of being able to rule, because his mind had remained lively for a long time. The body, however, was such as to prevent him from facing travel, hearings and all those continuous commitments. "We must consider that the calendar of a Pontiff, from a daily point of view, is extremely intense: we see the journeys, but the day is continuously marked by very strict commitments and also very delicate", concluded Cardinal Ravasi.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;

