AGI - Even the night between Wednesday and Thursday is spent serene for Francis. The Pope rose from the bed and had breakfast in the armchair. This is the latest update made known by the Vatican press room on the health of the Pontiff.&nbsp; The general picture remains complex as well as the drug therapy adopted and remoduled for the third time in five days. You should wait for the next few days to have more indications and certainties.
The condition of the Pope, admitted from last Friday to the Gemelli, continues to be "state". Vatican sources confirm the "prosecution of therapy" and report that the Pontiff also continues his "work activity", obviously carried out at low rates. The Pope continues to have the visits of his closest secretaries and collaborators who do the spolade between the Vatican and the Gemelli. The Pontiff "laws, writes, signs documents and calls". "At the moment there are no official visits,"
Although the clinical conditions of Pope Francis> continue to be stationary, blood tests "show a slight improvement, in particular inflammatory indexes". The situation, on the sixth day of shelter at the Gemelli hospital, would seem therefore, reading the medical bulletin issued by the Vatican press room, changed slightly in positive, after the cold shower of Tuesday, that is the occurrence of a bilateral pneumonia >, confirmed by a tac of control to the chest.
The Pontiff's mood continues to be good. In the afternoon of yesterday, around 15, he received privately the premier Giorgia Meloni.> A 20-minute meeting. In a note of Palazzo Chigi, Meloni reports that he found Bergoglio "vigile and reactive". "We've been joking like always. He did not lose his proverbial sense of humor," said the President of the Council, who also wanted to express on behalf of the nation the wishes for prompt healing.
<div </div
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, manifestations of affection and closeness continue to come from all over the world, accompanied by prayers for a prompt healing. Israeli president Isaac Herzog, during the meeting with the Jewish community in the synagogue of Rome, inaugurated "a ready and complete healing" recalling "his important words of condemnation of anti-Semitism".
From Jerusalem, Patriarch Pierbattista Pizzaballa invites the Pope to pray for the health of the Pope, and closeness has also been expressed by the Cei and the diocese of Rome, as well as the drawings that the small patients of the Oncology department of the Gemelli hospital delivered to him. And on the numerous "buffles" that these days circulate on the health of the Pope, Vatican sources say that "information is given regularly, fake news is commented on themselves". &nbsp;
