AGI - "The budgets we inherited, and does not say Francesco Rocca but the Prosecutor of the Republic says so, were ideologically false balances this is a fact. They were ideologically false because they applied to two police decrees so then the prosecutor says there is no personal but political responsibility over this." This was said by the president of the Lazio Region, Francesco Rocca, during a press conference for a budget of two years of regional government.
"The Court of Auditors, within the jurisdiction of the Regional Statement of 2022, has not certified the health accounts of 2022, with the consequent opening of two investigations of the judiciary, criminal and accounting - explained President Rocca - such was the state of uncertainty found in the accounting documents presented. So much so that the Prosecutor of the Republic of Rome, in the autumn of 2023, has started investigations on 8 General Directors, who, despite being asked for the archiving, have drafted "ideologically false balances" because of the "commissary Decrees 52/2017, 521/2018 and 297/2019. It is a political responsibility and not of a unionable criminal nature". &nbsp;
"We started with a negative projection of deficit of more than 700 million previewed for 2023, instead with a job that made clean in the budget - added Rocca - we obtained a reduction of negative endowment for approximately half billion euros, stating 475 million euros to the sanitary companies. We closed 2023 with 32 million profit and 2024 with 40 million profit".
"The opposition must rightly do its work but when it starts from data and false assumptions to criticize my administration it sorrows me. Sometimes I have this nuisance that, linked to my passion, makes me be excessively noisy when I get restless." President Francesco Rocca said. "This is a Region in return plan and all that is extra Lea can not return - it has concluded - it is useless to make demagogy and to say that Rocca and its junta are bad". &nbsp;
<h2> With Recup reform fell by 70% waiting time
"Recovery reform with integration into a single system of reservations, has gradually resulted in an increase in benefits provided and at the same time a reduction in waiting times: for those who booked a visit from 1 January 2025 to the present day (more than 700 thousand citizens who booked on the Recup), in 95.7% received an appointment in the guarantee times provided by the law". He illustrated Rocca.
"The percentage rises to 96.5% for the more than 470 thousand critical performances monitored and booked on the Recup - added Rocca - the average waiting time of January 2023-2024-2025 has been reduced from 31 days in 2023 to 9 days in 2025, with a reduction of 70% of the times, faced with an increase of more than 70 thousand performances delivered in January 2025 (356.201) than in January 2023 (280). &nbsp;
